    "body": "Yes. If i turn them off, kitty behaves slightly differently:\r\n\r\nThis is how it looks on startup\r\n![20231029_13h54m20s_grim](https://github.com/starship/starship/assets/64630479/976d40c9-3a71-4f91-b642-31bacbe4db34)\r\n\r\nThis is how it looks after running a command\r\n![20231029_13h54m34s_grim](https://github.com/starship/starship/assets/64630479/74e1cf6e-0c0f-4524-a215-1315e2d15316)\r\n\r\nI just noticed something: if i enter clear then it works as indended only so long as i keep the window on the present workspace. When i move it to another workspace, bring it back and start typing, it behaves as if it was started anew with the commandline at the bottom.\r\n\r\nI'm on NixOS unstable with kitty 0.30.1 and hyprland as the window manager.",
